<h2>
    Gear &amp; Techniques
</h2>
<ul>
    <li>
        <strong>Rods &amp; Lines</strong>:
        <ul>
            <li>
                Spinning: 9–10 ft medium-heavy, 12–20 lb braid + fluorocarbon leader 
            </li>
            <li>
                Fly: 7–8 wt rods with sink-tip lines for swing patterns 
            </li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Methods</strong>:
        <ol>
            <li>
                <strong>Drift fishing</strong> with roe or cured egg.
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Plunking</strong> with plugs like Spin‑N‑Glos near seams and eddies.
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Swinging flies</strong> (intruder, egg patterns) in tailouts and current seams 
            </li>
        </ol>
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Seasonal Adjustments</strong>:
        <ul>
            <li>
                Use bright lures in muddy winter flows; finesse tactics in summer 
            </li>
            <li>
                Focus on early morning and late afternoon bite windows .
            </li>
        </ul>
    </li>
</ul>
<h2>
    Licensing &amp; Regulations
</h2>
<ul>
    <li>
        <strong>Oregon fishing license</strong> plus <strong>Combined Angling Tag</strong> required.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Columbia Basin Endorsement</strong> needed for Sandy and Columbia fisheries 
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Hatchery vs. Wild</strong>: Only hatchery steelhead (adipose fin clipped) may be kept; wild steelhead are catch-and-release 
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Gear rules</strong>: Barbless hooks in some areas; bait rules vary by season&nbsp;
    </li>
</ul>
<h2>
    Local Smarter Tips
</h2>
<ul>
    <li>
        <strong>Bank fishing with kids</strong>? Try Oxbow Park on the Sandy—easy access, amenities, and fees that limit crowds 
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Check conditions</strong> via ODFW weekly fishing reports.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Prep gear</strong>: heavier braid for kings/steelhead, max 15–20 lb test 
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Ask local shops</strong> (e.g., Fisherman’s Marine) for current run status and best baits .
    </li>
</ul>
