    Final Thoughts
</h2>
<p>
    If you're near Gresham, your go-to steelhead waters are:
</p>
<ol>
    <li>
        <strong>Sandy River</strong> – best early winter &amp; summer steelhead close to town
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Clackamas River</strong> – strong hatchery returns and excellent access
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Lower Willamette</strong> – easy winter shore fishing at Meldrum Bar
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Columbia River</strong> – summer steelhead with broad access
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Wilson or Nestucca</strong> – for day-trippers after bigger wild steelhead
    </li>
</ol>
<p>
    Gear up properly, snag the needed licenses and endorsements, pick the right season, and you’ll find excellent steelhead action within easy reach of Gresham. Tight lines!
</p>

